messages.content: What is ComfyUI-Dart?
ComfyUI-Dart is a custom node for ComfyUI that adds nodes to generate danbooru tags using Dart (Danbooru Tags Transformer).
How can you install ComfyUI-Dart?
To install ComfyUI-Dart, navigate to the custom_nodes directory in your ComfyUI installation and run the command: git clone https://github.com/nkchocoai/ComfyUI-Dart.git
What does the 'Dart Load' node in ComfyUI-Dart do?
The 'Dart Load' node in ComfyUI-Dart loads the model and tokenizer for generating danbooru tags.
What is the purpose of the 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart generates danbooru tags using the Dart (Danbooru Tags Transformer) model.
How can you remove specific tags from the output of the 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart?
You can specify tags to be removed from the output of the 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart using the 'remove_tags' parameter.
What does the 'Dart Compose Prompt' node in ComfyUI-Dart do?
The 'Dart Compose Prompt' node in ComfyUI-Dart generates a prompt for the Dart Generate node that is compatible with the dart-v1 model.
What is the difference between the 'Dart Compose Prompt' and 'Dart Compose Prompt V2' nodes in ComfyUI-Dart?

The 'Dart Compose Prompt' node generates a prompt for the Dart Generate node that is compatible with the dart-v1 model, while the 'Dart Compose Prompt V2' node generates a prompt that is compatible with the dart-v2 model.
What is ComfyUI-Dart?
ComfyUI-Dart is a custom node for ComfyUI that adds nodes to generate Danbooru tags using Dart (Danbooru Tags Transformer).
How can ComfyUI-Dart be installed?
To install ComfyUI-Dart, navigate to the custom_nodes directory in the ComfyUI installation and run the command: git clone https://github.com/nkchocoai/ComfyUI-Dart.git
What does the 'Dart Generate' node do in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart generates Danbooru tags using the Dart (Danbooru Tags Transformer) model, while allowing the removal of specified tags using the 'remove_tags' parameter.
What is the purpose of the 'Dart Compose Prompt' and 'Dart Compose Prompt V2' nodes in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Compose Prompt' and 'Dart Compose Prompt V2' nodes in ComfyUI-Dart output the input 'prompt' for the Dart Generate node, with the former using dart-v1 and the latter using dart-v2.
How does the 'Dart Get Aspect Ratio' node work in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Get Aspect Ratio' node in ComfyUI-Dart outputs aspect ratio tags for dart-v2 prompts based on the provided width and height values.
What is the function of the 'Dart Ban Tags From Regex' node in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Ban Tags From Regex' node in ComfyUI-Dart outputs the input 'ban tags' for the Dart Generate node by searching with multiple regular expressions split into multiple lines.
How does the 'Dart Generate(Advanced)' node differ from the 'Dart Generate' node in ComfyUI-Dart?
The 'Dart Generate(Advanced)' node in ComfyUI-Dart outputs a token ID sequence of Danbooru tags generated by the Dart model, while the 'Dart Generate' node outputs the tags directly.
